@@TJvScrollText
<GROUP TJvScrollText>
Summary
  Can scroll multiple lines of text.
Description
  Use TJvScrollText to scroll multiple lines of text. 
  
  Use Items to specify the text. Use ScrollDirection to determine how text is scrolled within the 
  control. Use Delay to specify the interval between refresh events. Set Active to True to scroll the 
  text. 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Create
Summary
  Creates and initializes a new TJvScrollText object.
Description
  Call Create to create an instance of TJvScrollText at runtime. A TJvScrollText component placed on a 
  form at design time is created automatically.

  Pass a single Component as a parameter to provide the control with an Owner that is 
  responsible for freeing it.

  Create calls the inherited Create method, then sets the initial values for the control 
  as follows: 

  * Active is set to False.
  * Delay is set to 50.
  * ScrollPixels is set to 1.
  * ScrollDirection is set to drFromBottom.
Parameters
  AOwner - A component, typically the form, that is responsible for freeing the control.
See Also
  Destroy
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Destroy
Summary
  Destroys an instance of TJvScrollText.
Description
  Do not call Destroy directly in an application. Instead, call Free. Free verifies that the 
  TJvScrollText object is not nil and only then calls Destroy.
See Also
   Create
