@@TJvScrollThread
<GROUP TJvScrollText>
Summary
  Background thread for TJvScrollText control.
Description
  TJvScrollThread is the background thread that handles the timing of the movements. The Execute
  method will call the Draw method for each Delay, which in turn will call the control's
  Refresh method.

  Use TJvScrollText to scroll multiple lines of text. 
  
  Use Items to specify the text. Use ScrollDirection to determine how text is scrolled within the 
  control. Use Delay to specify the interval between refresh events. Set Active to True to scroll the 
  text. 

See Also
  TJvScrollText
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollThread.Draw
Summary
  Synchronize method.
Description
  Draw is the synchronized method to call the control's Refresh method. This will let the scroll text
  move to a new position.
Parameters
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollThread.Execute
Summary
  Thread's main code loop.
Description
  Execute is the thread's main code loop. It will delay for the specified amount (as set by the
  control) and then call's the Refresh method, using the synchronized Draw method.
Parameters
